177C 101st Legislative Session 177
2026 South Dakota Legislature
Senate Bill 177
AMENDME NT 177C
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Senator Blanc
1 An Act to require that a voter use a black ink pen when marking an optical scan
2 ballot clarify the requirements for marking an optical scan ballot.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
4 Section 1. That § 12-18-16.1 be AMENDED:
5 12-18-16.1. If an optical scan ballot is used, the voter may use a pencil or other
6 marking instrument provided must use a black ink ballpoint pen to mark the voter's choice
7 on the ballot person in charge of the election must:
8 (1) Provide a black ink pen for each in-person voter to mark the voter's choice on the
9 ballot; and
10 (2) Provide instructions to each voter who applies to vote by absentee ballot that the
11 voter use a black ink pen to mark the voter's choice on the ballot.
12 The person in charge of the election may not disqualify any ballot marked by a
13 writing instrument other than a black ink pen.
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

